{{Quote|Instead of being taken into the fold, I ended up here, in humiliated self-exile for failing to save Veruna's life.|Last words of Maris Magneta, former chief of [[Royal Naboo Security Forces/Legends|Royal Naboo Security Forces]], to Darth Maul|<ref name="End Game">{{StoryCite|story=End Game|book=Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace (novelization)|bformatted=''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'' novelization, 2012 edition}}</ref>}}
'''Maris Magneta''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] who served as chief of the [[Royal Naboo Security Forces/Legends|Royal Naboo Security Forces]] under [[King/Legends|King]] [[Ars Veruna/Legends|Ars Veruna]] of [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]]. After Veruna first abdicated in [[33 BBY/Legends|33 BBY]], then was [[Darth Plagueis/Legends#Dark Side death|assassinated]], Magneta stepped down; the new regent, [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]], replaced her with [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Quarsh Panaka/Legends|Quarsh Panaka]]. Although she didn't know how Veruna was assassinated, she did eventually find out that a [[Muunilinst/Legends|Muunilinst]] businessman named [[Darth Plagueis/Legends|Hego Damask]] and "his puppet" [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] were involved in the assassination.

Before the [[Invasion of Naboo/Legends|Invasion of Naboo]], Maris had learned of Damask's involvement, but she was later brutally murdered by [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]], who broke her neck. Maul&mdash;upon reflection, which left him disillusioned concerning points of "contract" and "honor"&mdash;was shocked that his [[Sith Master/Legends|Master]], Darth Sidious, would apparently break the [[Millennium/Legends|millennia]]-old [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Rule of Two/Legends|Rule of Two]] by taking on his own [[Sith apprentice/Legends|apprentice]] while two [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lords]] yet lived and were seemingly bound to one another by that ancient dark covenant.

